The paper deals with the quantum query complexity of subgraph isomorphism and homomorphism, which are fundamental problems in computer science and graph theory. The paper uses techniques from computational complexity, graph theory, and quantum computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic arguments, which suggest the sub-categories cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper discusses the critical probability of a graph, which is a topic in statistical physics and percolation theory, indicating the sub-category cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
